Download mongoDB  -> https://www.mongodb.com/download-center/community
go to mongofolder

npm init -y
npm install mongoose   //access to chemas and datatypes etc //makes working with mongoDB easier

//schema is a structured way of storing data

$ means the teminal

run mongodb

FIRST TERMINAL ->
cd C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\4.2\bin
mongod

SECOND TERMINAL (RUN MONGOSHELL)->
cd C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\4.2\bin
mongo //runs the mongo
show dbs // shows where the memory is being allocated
use signup //in the index.js we have allocated the database name to signup and we are now accessing it (mongoose.connect('mongodb://localhost:27017/signup',{)
db.users.find().pretty() //this displacys all the queries

THIRD TERMINAL ->
locate the file
node index.js //runs the program